## API Integration
- Base URL: http://localhost:8080
- All API calls go through src/lib/api.ts
- Handle token refresh automatically
- Backend project is in ../learnmore-go - check it for endpoint details

## Error Handling & Placeholders
- ALWAYS implement proper error handling with try-catch
- If an image/asset is missing, create CSS placeholder and log warning
- If API returns error, show user-friendly message and log details
- After completing tasks, report any warnings about missing assets or API issues
- If backend endpoint doesn't match, check ../learnmore-go and suggest fixes

## Important Patterns
1. Always handle loading and error states
2. Use skeleton loaders for better UX
3. Check for file existence before creating
4. WebSocket for real-time features with REST fallback
5. Responsive design (mobile-first)

## Authentication Flow
- JWT tokens stored in localStorage
- Refresh token mechanism
- Protected routes via layout auth check
- OAuth support (GitHub, Google)

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (UserDashboard.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with 'use' prefix (useAuth.ts)
- Utils: camelCase (formatDate.ts)
- Types: PascalCase (User, AuthResponse)
- API functions: camelCase (getUserProfile)